X i is a forget bag. Let X j = X i ∪ { v } be the child of X i . The algorithm computes R i by exhaustively merging records of R j as follows.

1. For each R p j ∈ R j , we remove from O p j and A p j all the edges incident to v and from P p j and F p j all the pairs where one of the vertices is v . Observe that due to this operation, there might now be records that are identical except possibly for their costs. Among them, we only keep one record whose cost is no larger than any other record.

